<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
Plants usually medium-sized, not slender, of a ± robust habit, base with a tunic or with a few old petioles, or without tunic. Petiole winged, usually broadly winged in outer and middle leaves, not winged in later, inner leaves; leaf blade pinnatisect; lateral lobes few to numerous, usually triangular to narrowly triangular, patent to ± recurved, margin entire or (usually on interlobes) often dentate or lobulate. Capitulum usually (2.5–) 3–3.5 (–4) cm wide. Outer phyllaries usually 12–20, lanceolate to broadly ovate, long, often imbricate, appressed, loosely appressed, or less often arcuaterecurved, usually distinctly broadly or narrowly bordered, apex flat to corniculate. Ligules yellow; floret tube glabrous. Achene red, reddish brown, brown, castaneous, cinnamon or light greyish stramineous-brown, usually 
<quantity box="[1315,1452,1072,1099]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="4.9" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.3">4.3–5.5 mm</quantity>
long; body usually densely spinulose above, usually subabruptly to subgradually narrowing into a distinct cylindric (0.5–) 
<quantity box="[211,325,1144,1171]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
cone, spinules long and thin; beak usually 
<quantity box="[807,936,1144,1171]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" unit="cm" value="1.05" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.3 cm</quantity>
. Pappus ± white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
Members of 
<emphasis box="[347,368,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode box="[347,364,1181,1206]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[446,597,1180,1206]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Erythrocarpa">
<emphasis box="[446,597,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are agamospermous, with a single exception, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" baseAuthorityName="Baldacci" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[1165,1306,1180,1206]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pindicola">
<emphasis box="[1165,1306,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. pindicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Within the distribution area of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" baseAuthorityName="Baldacci" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[353,486,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pindicola">
<emphasis box="[353,486,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. pindicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or in its vicinity, the variation pattern of 
<emphasis box="[936,957,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode box="[936,953,1217,1242]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[1019,1170,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Erythrocarpa">
<emphasis box="[1019,1170,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
follows the geographical parthenogenesis model (Hörandl 2006), and several agamospermous species are morphologically close to the variable sexual taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
About 45 species are known to belong to 
<emphasis box="[642,664,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode box="[642,659,1325,1350]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[724,875,1324,1350]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Erythrocarpa">
<emphasis box="[724,875,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, occurring in the northern Mediterranean and Irano-Turanian regions, including 
<collectingCountry box="[457,524,1360,1386]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[536,588,1360,1386]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Italy</collectingCountry>
, Balkan Peninsula, the Black Sea region, 
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1145,1360,1386]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1202,1250,1361,1387]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Iran</collectingCountry>
, and occasionally are found outside that area (the Western Carpathians, the Caucasus, 
<collectingCountry box="[939,987,1397,1423]" name="Iraq" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1000,1140,1396,1422]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1155,1227,1396,1423]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">China</collectingCountry>
). The section, both morphologically and on the basis of molecular analyses, is close to 
<emphasis box="[919,941,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode box="[919,936,1433,1458]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1009,1178,1432,1458]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrosperma</emphasis>
(smaller achenes, outer phyllaries usually not appressed, without border or with a less distinct border, leaf shape more complicated). Another similar but geographically remote group is 
<emphasis box="[617,638,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode box="[617,634,1505,1530]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="van Soest (1966: 377" authorityName="van Soest" authorityYear="1966" box="[701,1042,1504,1531]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Dissecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[701,797,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Dissecta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="van Soest, J. L." box="[804,1042,1504,1531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="364 - 377" refId="ref39345" refString="van Soest, J. L. (1966) New species of Taraxacum from Asia I, II. Proceedings, Koniklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen, ser. C, 69 (3): 364 - 377 (I) et 378 - 388 (II)." type="journal article" year="1966">van Soest (1966: 377</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, for a more detailed information, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ge, X. J. &amp; Kirschner, J. &amp; Stepanek, J." box="[136,295,1540,1566]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="270 - 325" refId="ref37572" refString="Ge, X. J., Kirschner, J. &amp; Stepanek, J. (2011) Taraxacum F. H. Wiggers. In: Wu, Z. Y., Raven, P. H. &amp; Hong, D. Y. (Ed.) Flora of China, Vols. 20 - 21. St. Louis, Missouri Botanical Garden Press &amp; Beijing, Science Press, pp. 270 - 325." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Ge 
<emphasis box="[175,230,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), and there are also morphological links to 
<emphasis box="[770,791,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode box="[770,787,1541,1566]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[853,951,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scariosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[853,951,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Scariosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sonck" authorityYear="1989" box="[1022,1213,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panhellenicum">
<emphasis box="[1022,1213,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. panhellenicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the species closest to intersectional intermediates, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlstedt (1926: 6)" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityPageNumber="6" authorityYear="1926" box="[542,896,1575,1602]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graecum">
<emphasis box="[542,667,1577,1602]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. graecum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[674,896,1575,1602]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref37200" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1926) Uber einige orientalische Taraxacum-Arten. Acta Horti Bergiani 9 (1): 1 - 36 + 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1926">Dahlstedt (1926: 6)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
Since 1985, we re-defined 
<emphasis box="[485,506,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode box="[485,502,1613,1638]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dahlstedt 1909: 172) Dahlstedt (1921: 37)" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityPageNumber="37" authorityYear="1921" baseAuthorityName="Dahlstedt" baseAuthorityPageNumber="172" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[568,1146,1612,1638]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Obliqua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[568,660,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Obliqua</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[673,900,1612,1638]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="167 - 179" refId="ref37127" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1909) Nya skandinaviska Taraxacum-arter. Botaniska Notiser 1909: 167 - 179. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 211121  page / 507 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1909">Dahlstedt 1909: 172</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[914,1146,1612,1638]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref37169" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1921) De svenska arterna av slaktet Taraxacum. I. Erythrosperma, II. Obliqua. Acta Florae Sueciae 1: 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1921">Dahlstedt (1921: 37)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, another related and similar group, originally including only two agamospermous species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fries 1814: 14) Dahlstedt (1905: 152" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityYear="1814" baseAuthorityName="Fries" baseAuthorityPageNumber="14" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[860,1451,1648,1675]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obliquum">
<emphasis box="[860,998,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. obliquum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fries, E. M." box="[1016,1188,1648,1674]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refId="ref37484" refString="Fries, E. M. (1814) Novitiae florae suecicae, Vol. 1. Berling, Lundae, 22 pp." type="book" year="1814">Fries 1814: 14</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[1207,1451,1648,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="145 - 172" refId="ref37085" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1905) Om skandinaviska Taraxacumformer. Botaniska Notiser 1905: 145 - 172. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 210848  page / 1 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1905">Dahlstedt (1905: 152</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
&amp; 164) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Raunkiaer (1906: 256)" authorityName="Raunkiaer" authorityPageNumber="256" authorityYear="1906" box="[281,730,1684,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyglossum">
<emphasis box="[281,459,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. platyglossum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Raunkiaer, C. C." box="[469,730,1684,1711]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refId="ref38501" refString="Raunkiaer, C. C. (1906) Dansk Exkursions-Flora [...]. Gyldendalske Boghandel Nordisk Forlag, Kjobenhavn og Kristiania, 286 pp." type="book" year="1906">Raunkiaer (1906: 256)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but now understood as a group centered around the sexual 
<taxonomicName authority="Reuter (1861: 4)" authorityName="Reuter" authorityPageNumber="4" authorityYear="1861" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrenaicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. pyrenaicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Reuter, G. F." box="[275,462,1720,1747]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refId="ref38528" refString="Reuter, G. F. (1861) Catalogue des graines recueillies en 1861 et offertes en echange par le Jardin botanique de Geneve. Impr. Ramboz &amp; Schuchart, Geneve, 4 pp." type="book" year="1861">Reuter (1861: 4)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and covering not only the two coastal species but also a number of similar plants from the Western Alps and adjacent areas, mainly in 
<collectingCountry box="[673,753,1757,1783]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">France</collectingCountry>
. Thus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hand." authorityName="Hand." box="[834,1062,1756,1782]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilonare">
<emphasis box="[834,985,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. aquilonare</emphasis>
Hand.
</taxonomicName>
